Rapper Riki Rick, whose real name is Rikhado Makhado recently opened the doors to his new barbershop - Legends Barbershop in Waterfall Midrand. The Unisex salon is the rappers new business venture which is open 7 days a week. Industry friends such as internationally renowned DJ, Black Coffee showed support for the Rapper, urging fans to head to the barbershop for a good haircut. DJ Sbu, Nasty C and Mampintsha are also a few artists who have been spotted showing support to their Riki. Riki Rick has been sharing a few snaps on Instagram thanking everyone who has been supporting him. Legends Barbershop also offered exclusive mobile services at the Durban July giving some stars fresh cuts. ??@legends_barber WATERFALL CORNER is officially open??7 days a week??? ? Mon-Fri: 9am - 6pm? Sat: 8am - 6pm? Sun: 8:30am - 1pm? Public Holidays: 8:30am - 1pm? ? #legendsbarbershop #legendsbarbershopwaterfall #thelegendaryexperience A post shared by  Rikhado "Riky Rick" Makhado (@rikyrickworld) on Jul 2, 2019 at 1:53am PDT  Thank you to everyone who came through for the opening day of @legends_barber WATERFALL CORNER ?????? we promise to keep you fresh at all times. 7 days a week. A post shared by  Rikhado "Riky Rick" Makhado (@rikyrickworld) on Jun 28, 2019 at 2:43pm PDT  Thank you @realblackcoffee for always supporting me. Your guidance and knowledge inspires me to be the best person I can be. Thank you big man. Goodluck for the rest of your tour ???? A post shared by  Rikhado "Riky Rick" Makhado (@rikyrickworld) on Jun 28, 2019 at 4:57am PDT  Being well groomed is a sign of confidence. #BrutEssenceOfMan #DurbanJuly2019 #TLB ??: @moonflare_ A post shared by  Legends Barbershop ™? (@legends_barber) on Jul 6, 2019 at 9:18am PDT   